assume fib(n) = a^n + b^n

fib(n-1) + fib(n) = fib(n+1)   <=>
a^n + a^n-1 = a^n+1 or a^2 = a + 1
-b^n - b^n-1 = -b^n+1 or b^2 = b + 1

Therefore a, b = (1+sqrt(5))/2, (1-sqrt(5))/2 is fine 
also: fib(0) = (1-1)/sqrt(5) = 0
      fib(1) = 2*sqrt(5)/2/sqrt(5) = 1
==> Fib(n) = (a^n - b^n) / sqrt(5)


absolute value of b^n/sqrt(5) < 1/2 (obvious)